                " There are two key challenges in Federated Learning that differentiate it from traditional distributed optimization: (1) significant variability in terms of the systemâ€™s characteristics on each device in the network (systems heterogeneity), and (2) non-identically distributed data across the network (statistical heterogeneity). FedProx (Tian Li ",
                "et al",
                ".",
                " ",
